--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
OpenBSD
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The OpenBSD Project (https://www.openbsd.org/) supplies the base
operating system that runs on the DM250. Kernel patches under
`kernel-patches/` modify files from the upstream OpenBSD source tree and
inherit the ISC license used by that tree. See `LICENSE-ISC` and
https://www.openbsd.org/policy.html for the canonical license terms.

Acknowledgement of the OpenBSD developers does not imply that this
project is endorsed by the OpenBSD Project.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
jcs / openbsd-src (rk3128 branch)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
joshua stein's rk3128 branch of openbsd-src
(https://github.com/jcs/openbsd-src) provides the bring-up patches that
made OpenBSD run on the DM250 in the first place. The patches in
`kernel-patches/` are layered on top of that branch. License: BSD/ISC,
inherited from the OpenBSD source files being modified.

joshua stein's write-up "Installing OpenBSD on the Pomera DM250"
(https://jcs.org/2024/01/15/dm250) is the primary reference for the
hardware bring-up procedure.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
armbian Broadcom firmware
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The AP6212 / BCM4343A1 Bluetooth firmware blob (referenced by the
install steps under `install/` and consumed by `panctl/`) originates from
the armbian-firmware tree
(https://github.com/armbian/firmware/tree/master/ap6212). It is
redistributed by Broadcom / Cypress under their respective firmware
license terms. This project does not re-license the firmware; consult
the armbian and Broadcom/Cypress sources for the canonical terms.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
BlueKitchen BTstack
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The Bluetooth PAN daemon under `panctl/` is built on top of BlueKitchen
BTstack v1.6.2 (https://github.com/bluekitchen/btstack). BTstack is
distributed by BlueKitchen GmbH under a BSD-style license; for
non-commercial / open source use the terms in the upstream `LICENSE`
file apply. Commercial users should contact BlueKitchen directly.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Linux RK818 driver (reference only)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The OCV (open-circuit voltage) curve and calibration constants used by
the battery PS1 helper under `battery/` were derived by reading the
upstream Linux RK818 PMIC / fuel-gauge drivers
(`drivers/mfd/rk808.c`, `drivers/power/supply/rk818_battery.c`).
That code is licensed under the GNU General Public License v2. **No GPL
source is redistributed here**: only numeric constants and behavioural
observations were used, in a clean-room rewrite. The `battery/` shell
helpers themselves are MIT-licensed.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
EKESETE eMMC backup tool (ichinomoto)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The initial DM250 eMMC bring-up flow relies on the EKESETE eMMC backup
tool by ichinomoto, used to capture a full image of the factory eMMC
before any destructive operation. This repository does **not** bundle
that tool; `install/` documents how to obtain and run it separately.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Inconsolata Nerd Font (referenced for terminal display)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Recommended Nerd Font glyphs (FA4 PUA range) used by the battery PS1
prompt come from the Nerd Fonts project
(https://github.com/ryanoasis/nerd-fonts). Glyphs and metadata are
redistributed by upstream under their original licenses (typically OFL).
Only references and code points are used here; no font files are
bundled in this repository.

